BOHZ's 1H net profit rose \(16.7\%\) YoY to RMB11.7bn (vs. up \(17.3\%\) in 1Q), in line with pre- guidance. PPOP grew \(4.8\%\) YoY in 1H, faster than \(+2.9\%\) YoY in 1Q. The robust earnings growth in 1H was mainly boosted by \(28\%\) decline in loan provisioning and \(3.5\%\) increase in non- loan write- back. ROE fell 1.2ppt YoY to \(18.6\%\) in 1H. CET1 ratio rose by 111bp YoY or 89bp HoH to \(9.74\%\) in 1H25 after the completion of CB conversion. We tweak down our earnings estimates by \(1 - 2\%\) to reflect the results, lower cost of capital by 100bp on the enhanced capital strength, and lower PO by \(10\%\) to CNY16.02 (to reflect the dilution impact), now based on 0.80x 2025- 26E P/B, assuming average ROE of \(15.2\%\) , a medium- term growth rate of \(4.0\%\) , and a cost of equity of \(18.0\%\) (vs prior \(0.82x\) , \(16.2\%\) , \(4.0\%\) , \(19.0\%\) respectively). Reiterate Neutral rating given its current valuation is fair, in our view.

Net interest income (NII) up \(1.3\%\) QoQ, with gross interest income/expense up \(0.5\%\) or down \(0.1\%\) QoQ. NIM est. fell by 3bp QoQ in 2Q to \(1.34\%\) or - 5bp HoH to \(1.35\%\) in 1H on both lower asset yield (- 31bp HoH) and lower funding cost (- 19bp HoH). The maturity lengthening largely stabilized with demand mix at \(39\%\) by 1H25. Loans grew \(1.4\%\) QoQ or \(12.0\%\) YoY (vs. \(+16.5\%\) in 1H24), with loans to utilities, manufacturing, leasing & commercial services, and retail loans accounting for \(37\% /34\% /29\% / - 9\%\) of the net new loans in 1H, vs. \(37\% /14\% /19\% /18\%\) in 1H24. Assets grew \(0.6\%\) QoQ or \(12.6\%\) YoY. Deposits fell \(0.8\%\) QoQ on seasonality or grew \(16.2\%\) YoY, with deposit cost declining from \(2.08\% /2.04\%\) in 1H/FY24 to \(1.80\%\) in 1H25. Loan- deposit ratio fell YoY to \(75.4\%\) in 1H. Fee income rose \(11\%\) YoY in 1H (vs. \(+22.2\%\) in 1Q). Other non- interest income decline narrowed from - \(18.5\%\) YoY in 1Q to - \(11.6\%\) in 1H25. Revenue grew \(4.0\%\) YoY in 1H (vs up \(2.3\%\) in 1Q), operating cost rose \(1.6\%\) YoY, and CIR edged down to \(25.4\%\)

NPL size rose \(1.0\%\) QoQ and NPL ratio was stable at \(0.76\%\) . SML ratio edged down 3bp QoQ to \(0.51\%\) . Corp loan NPL ratio fell by 10bp HoH to \(0.65\%\) while retail loan NPL ratio up by 25bp HoH to \(1.02\%\) (mortgage/personal business/consumption at \(0.46\% /1.28\% /1.46\%\) ). Gross NPL formation edged down to 50bp in 1H, lower than 53bp in 1H24 or 66bp in FY24. Credit cost fell from 107bp/97bp in 1H/FY24 to 68bp in 1H25. NPL/loan reserve coverage ratio fell 9ppt QoQ/9bp QoQ to \(521\%\) and \(3.95\%\) , both high.

BOHZ is a top 10 city commercial bank in China by total assets/loans/deposits. It has been expanding businesses beyond Hangzhou city, and has set up 15 branches outside Hangzhou, including 10 in Zhejiang Province and one each in Shanghai, Beijing, Guangdong, Jiangsu and Anhui Province. BOHZ's shareholding structure is diversified with no controlling shareholders, but its actual controller is Hangzhou Municipal Bureau of Finance.

We rate BOHZ at Neutral. On the positive side, BOHZ is well positioned in the developed regions in China. It has good asset quality and high provision coverage. We expect it to achieve strong pre- provision profit growth and net profit in 2025- 27E. On the negative side, its lending is concentrated to infrastructure and the growth is likely to slow down, yet new business developments may face multiple uncertainties. Its tight capital may also constrain growth.

At our PO, the stock would be trading at \(5.6x 2025 - 26E P / E\) or \(3.7x 2025 - 26E P / PPO\) .
Downside risks are slow new business development, local services, LGFV risks, economy slowdown, potential private placement and deteriorating asset quality.
Upside risks are better- than- expected new business development, better- than- expected margin trend and lower- than- expected credit costs.
